gation throughout the galaxy. With\nthese improvements, we find that the five models for the atomic-to-molecular\ntransition roughly agree on average but that the details of the modeling matter\nfor individual galaxies and the spatial distribution of molecular hydrogen. We\nemphasize that the estimated molecular fractions are approximate due to the\nsignificant systematic uncertainties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Jun 2018 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 23 Oct 2018 18:40:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-25"}
