isions we find that the critical velocity is larger than $v_L$ and the drag\nforce (per cross-sectional area) at $2v_L$ is reduced by an order of magnitude\ncompared to the case of a small object. In a collision-dominated limit the flow\nshows signs of instability at a velocity below $v_L$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Jun 2018 08:11:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 29 Jun 2018 11:12:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-24"}
